{"comments":"Submodular Function Types with Phantom Monotonicity\n\nA function f: 2^V → ℝ is submodular if for all A ⊆ B ⊆ V and x ∉ B:\n  f(A ∪ {x}) - f(A) ≥ f(B ∪ {x}) - f(B)\n\nThis is the \"diminishing returns\" property: adding an element to a smaller\nset provides at least as much gain as adding it to a larger set.\n\n## Monotonicity as Phantom Type\n\nWe use phantom types `Monotone` and `NonMonotone` to track function properties\nat compile time. This ensures we cannot accidentally use a non-monotone function\nwhere a monotone one is required for correctness guarantees.\n\n- Monotone + Matroid: Greedy achieves (1 - 1/e) ≈ 0.632 approximation\n- Non-monotone: Best known is 1/2 approximation\n\n## Curvature as Value\n\nCurvature κ ∈ [0,1] is value-level because it's typically computed from\nthe function's parameters, not statically known. κ = 0 means modular (linear),\nκ = 1 means maximally curved (steepest diminishing returns).\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Render","Online","Submodular","Function"],"IsMonotoneFn"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Render","Online","Submodular","Function"],"Monotone"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[232,22],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[231,1]},"title":"isMonotoneFnMonotone"}],"comments":"Phantom type marker for monotone submodular functions\n\nA function f is monotone if: A ⊆ B implies f(A) ≤ f(B)\nThis guarantees (1 - 1/e) approximation with greedy + matroid.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[91,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[91,1]},"title":"Monotone"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Render","Online","Submodular","Function"],"IsMonotoneFn"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Render","Online","Submodular","Function"],"NonMonotone"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[235,23],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[234,1]},"title":"isMonotoneFnNonMonotone"}],"comments":"Phantom type marker for non-monotone submodular functions\n\nNon-monotone functions may decrease when adding elements.\nBest known approximation is 1/2.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[97,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[97,1]},"title":"NonMonotone"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Render","Online","Core"],"BoundedNumber"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[113,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[113,19]},"title":"Curvature"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Render","Online","Submodular","Function"],"Curvature"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[115,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[115,1]},"title":"eqCurvature"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Render","Online","Submodular","Function"],"Curvature"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[116,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[116,1]},"title":"ordCurvature"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Render","Online","Submodular","Function"],"Curvature"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[119,71],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[118,1]},"title":"showCurvature"}],"comments":"Curvature parameter κ ∈ [0, 1]\n\nCurvature measures the \"steepness\" of diminishing returns:\n\n- κ = 0: Modular (linear) — no diminishing returns\n- κ = 1: Maximally curved — steepest diminishing returns\n\nFor a monotone submodular function with curvature κ, greedy achieves\nat least (1 - κ/e) approximation, which is tighter than (1 - 1/e)\nwhen κ < 1.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[113,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[113,1]},"title":"Curvature"},{"children":[],"comments":"Construct curvature within valid bounds\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Maybe"],"Maybe"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Render","Online","Submodular","Function"],"Curvature"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[122,41],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Render/Online/Submodular/Function.purs","start":[122,1]},"title":"mkCurvature"},{"children":[],"comments":"Extract the curv